transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Bianca, Joanna speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: I ordered some pills, I've been trying to, I had pill therapy treatment and it made me all fucked up.

Speaker 1: And I ordered some pills from different people, but the pill that I ordered from y'all never came, it's been over a month.

Speaker 2: Almost a month anyway, three or four weeks anyway.

Speaker 1: If I knew that, I'd have ordered back from them where I was doing it.

Speaker 2: And I was trying different pills that maybe I could get straightened out.

Speaker 1: And I said, why didn't I go to the phone?

Speaker 2: The post office keeps saying a bunch of crap and they talk about the weather.

Speaker 1: How the hell is the weather in the sunshine?

Speaker 2: Are you there?

Speaker 1: No, I'm listening to you sir, but you lost me when you started talking about the weather.

Speaker 2: What was that?

Speaker 1: The post office, I got a thing for the delivery and they said the weather or something.

Speaker 2: But they've been saying the same thing for weeks.

Speaker 1: I tried calling them, but I can't get a response.

Speaker 2: I don't know if y'all didn't send it or what could be going on.

Speaker 1: We sent it out on February 4th.

Speaker 2: Huh?

Speaker 1: We sent it out on February 4th, so you are right.

Speaker 2: That's a long time ago.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I know, I do see that sir, that there is a delay due to the weather condition.

Speaker 2: Weather, weather, weather in the United States?

Speaker 1: I don't know nowhere in the United States we got bad weather.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so the U.S. Coastal Service site says winter weather in north central, north eastern U.S.

Speaker 1: May delay final delivery of your mail and packages.

Speaker 2: So that's what they're saying.

Speaker 1: I'm not sure.

Speaker 2: I'm in California, so we clearly don't know.

Speaker 1: They won't do nothing.

Speaker 2: It's been weeks and weeks.

Speaker 1: No, I'm going to help you out, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you a replacement order.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm going to send you another shipment out.

Speaker 2: Hopefully there's no delays with this order.

Speaker 1: I do apologize.

Speaker 2: It is the U.S. Coastal Service that has created this delay.

Speaker 1: So I'll go ahead and, as a courtesy, ship it out to you again.

Speaker 2: How long should it take for me to get it?

Speaker 1: Typically it takes two to five business days.

Speaker 2: It ships out of Kentucky.

Speaker 1: Okay, that would be great.

Speaker 2: I'm going to say something.

Speaker 1: I don't want to disrespect anybody, but you're a girl.

Speaker 2: I had to take prostate cancer treatment, but I'm done with the treatment,

Speaker 1: and it made me all messed up.

Speaker 2: I'm trying to take care of my girl before I lose her all the way.

Speaker 1: You understand that, don't you?

Speaker 2: I do understand that.

Speaker 1: That's why I say girls like me.

Speaker 2: I said we don't want that.

Speaker 1: I'm here to help.

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: Well, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it so much.

Speaker 1: A girl can go in and work it out, though.

Speaker 2: She's having a fit.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Mr. Sharp, just real quick, so we don't have any issues with this next shipment.

Speaker 1: I just want to confirm your shipping address.

Speaker 2: Is it still 3240 North Keystone Ave.?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: It is?

Speaker 1: Okay, and that's in Indianapolis, IN, and then 46218?

Speaker 2: Yes, exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll have another order sent out to you today, okay?

Speaker 1: All right, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Of course.

Speaker 1: Thanks for calling.

Speaker 2: And I will be doing that.

Speaker 1: I had yesterday of knockouts.

Speaker 2: Then I had to take five or six of them.

Speaker 1: I didn't like that.

Speaker 2: But, okay, I hope this will work out better.

Speaker 1: Yes, and just remember to take it on an empty stomach.

Speaker 2: Viagra is recommended to not take it with a heavy meal.

Speaker 1: Otherwise, it's not going to work as well.

Speaker 2: I'm glad you said that.

Speaker 1: I didn't know that.

Speaker 2: I'm glad you said that.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you so much.

Speaker 1: First thing in the morning or, like, several hours before a meal or several hours after a meal.

Speaker 2: But just not with a big, heavy meal.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: You have a nice day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: My pleasure.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye.
